Resolution congratulating Library Director Barbara Kerr on her retirement.

17
00:05:43,739 --> 00:05:51,882
Be it resolved by the Medford City Council that we congratulate Barbara Kerr on her retirement as Director of the Medford Public Library and thank her for over 40 years of public service to the City of Medford.

18
00:05:52,897 --> 00:06:00,779
So pretty self-explanatory resolution in some ways, but I don't think there's any short way to describe the impact that Barbara Kerr has had on our community.

19
00:06:01,360 --> 00:06:04,580
Barbara has been at the Medford Public Library for decades.

20
00:06:05,061 --> 00:06:08,902
She is instrumental in receiving the, making sure that we received the,

21
00:06:10,416 --> 00:06:13,357
State Library Commissioner's Award to build the new Medford Public Library.

22
00:06:13,457 --> 00:06:28,064
And then also for the past now almost five years to open that library, to fund that library, to bring in additional funding from the members of the community and foundations to support programs at the library.

23
00:06:28,104 --> 00:06:31,846
And the library is more than ever just at the heart of our community.

24
00:06:31,926 --> 00:06:34,087
So Barbara has done so much for our city.

25
00:06:35,147 --> 00:06:35,908
She has been

26
00:06:36,848 --> 00:06:44,320
an amazing public servant, and she is having a retirement party this Friday at the library at 3 o'clock, so I hope that folks can attend.

27
00:06:45,001 --> 00:06:50,230
And we're going to get this resolution, assuming you all pass it, and I'll tell her who's responsible if we don't.

28
00:06:52,763 --> 00:06:59,009
pass this citation and get it on some paper and I'll bring it down and share it with her at her party on Friday.

29
00:06:59,769 --> 00:07:05,355
She's just been such an important figure here in our community and we're so thankful for her decades of service.

30
00:07:06,135 --> 00:07:08,978
Councillor Singh.

31
00:07:09,058 --> 00:07:18,787
I mean, I think President Behrs, you really stated well the number of big projects that she's worked on for our city that

32
00:07:19,513 --> 00:07:28,657
families in Medford, that kids in Medford, that residents of all ages, seniors, and those who need internet access have, you know, really benefited from.

33
00:07:29,518 --> 00:07:32,699
Barbara's been there for longer than I've been alive.

34
00:07:34,280 --> 00:07:39,222
Her impact on the library is something that you see day in and day out.

35
00:07:39,342 --> 00:07:40,583
I remember when the library was

36
00:07:41,308 --> 00:07:45,670
running on twine and she kept it together.

37
00:07:46,670 --> 00:07:50,392
She was instrumental in shepherding in our new library.

38
00:07:51,293 --> 00:08:00,797
She is the godmother of the Medford Public Library and our community will be forever in debt to her service.

39
00:08:02,532 --> 00:08:13,602
I, you know, I'm really deeply grateful that not only does she have the, you know, has she had the energy to keep up a really complicated library system that we have here at Medford.

40
00:08:14,162 --> 00:08:21,809
She's gone up and, up and above in reaching out to us as counselors when it came to advocating for the library budget.

41
00:08:22,049 --> 00:08:27,394
When it came to keeping us updated and tying us, linking us to the board of trustees.

42
00:08:27,894 --> 00:08:33,981
to make sure that every one of us knew what was going on at the library on a month-to-month basis.

43
00:08:34,401 --> 00:08:45,013
And because of that hard work that she puts in after hours, our library is now a stellar shining star in our community.

44
00:08:45,514 --> 00:08:47,956
So the impact is huge.

45
00:08:48,832 --> 00:08:58,358
They're huge shoes to fill, but I think all of us here in Medford can be really deeply grateful to Barbara's service to our city.

