334
00:27:19,052 --> 00:27:24,416
26070, resolution to invite the residents of Brooks Park to discuss their experience with rats.

335
00:27:24,556 --> 00:27:34,144
Whereas the Tenant Association of the Brooks Park Apartments have been living with a rat infestation since they first formed in March 2024, with residents experiencing frequent sightings of rats behind the building in the parking lot.

336
00:27:35,065 --> 00:27:45,353
hearing rats living in the dumpster when throwing away trash, rats on the fire escape outside windows, rat holes along the front of the building, rats in the basement and laundry room, and rats in the city park across the building.

337
00:27:45,894 --> 00:28:00,965
And whereas the Tenant Association sent a request to Charles Gate Property Management requesting simple fixes to the heightened levels of rat infestation as detailed in the attached letter from December 2025, notably replacement of inadequate and unused dumpsters with new ones that close tightly, including those with a locked lid and side door.

338
00:28:01,846 --> 00:28:11,713
removal of unused dumpers such as the one that is sealed shut, more frequent trash collection, professional exterminator services, plugging rat holes in front of the building, and collaborating with the city in eradicating rats from the park.

339
00:28:12,234 --> 00:28:27,024
Whereas Charlesgate has not taken adequate steps to meet these requests since the letter was sent in December, now therefore be it resolved by the Medford City Council that the residents of Brooks Park Apartments and Charlesgate be invited, as well as representatives from the Board of Health, be invited to the City Council to speak about their experiences on the matter.

340
00:28:27,104 --> 00:28:27,665
Councilor Lemming.

341
00:28:29,536 --> 00:28:37,024
Thank you, Council President Behrs, and thank you to the residents of Brooks Park Apartments who have come to the City Council meeting to speak.

342
00:28:37,604 --> 00:28:39,987
I have a small presentation here.

343
00:28:40,047 --> 00:28:48,035
It's mostly just pictures that I took of the last two or three times I've gone to meet with the residents of Brooks Park Apartments.

344
00:28:48,996 --> 00:28:53,220
I'm going to send a request to share.

345
00:28:59,187 --> 00:29:00,194
All right.

346
00:29:06,207 --> 00:29:07,788
We got this right here.

347
00:29:07,808 --> 00:29:07,848
OK.

348
00:29:09,189 --> 00:29:10,330
So these are these are a couple.

349
00:29:10,390 --> 00:29:11,190
So I've gone.

350
00:29:11,210 --> 00:29:13,652
OK so a little bit of background.

351
00:29:14,312 --> 00:29:28,262
Brooks Park Apartments was purchased by Charles Gate property managers a couple of years ago and they've purchased a few properties around the city and have developed a bit of a

352
00:29:29,042 --> 00:29:32,865
bit of a reputation for being unresponsive to residents' claims.

353
00:29:32,965 --> 00:29:41,592
I did invite them to this meeting, and they said that they didn't have adequate notice to attend, which I think is fair.

354
00:29:42,813 --> 00:29:48,497
But so it should be noted that when I did reach out to them, they did respond to me.

355
00:29:48,597 --> 00:29:55,843
Also in this agenda is a letter that the residents of Brooks Park sent to Charles Gates listing a couple of

356
00:29:56,983 --> 00:30:01,346
A couple of requests that they had for fixing the situation.

357
00:30:01,386 --> 00:30:09,110
But essentially, the residents of Brooks Park have been living pretty consistently with rat infestations.

358
00:30:09,290 --> 00:30:13,072
Residents have noted that they're frequently in the dumpsters.

359
00:30:13,112 --> 00:30:14,973
They see them on the fire escapes all the time.

360
00:30:15,033 --> 00:30:16,754
They see them in the basement under the building.

361
00:30:17,915 --> 00:30:20,796
And there's a couple, and the Board of Health is long on this.

362
00:30:20,876 --> 00:30:23,598
They've been doing what they can to amend the situation.

363
00:30:23,618 --> 00:30:31,003
But at the end of the day, this is a case of a landlord that needs to do a couple of very simple things to fix this situation.

364
00:30:31,043 --> 00:30:37,487
And they simply have not been putting the investment in these properties that they need to.

365
00:30:37,547 --> 00:30:41,190
So, picture it here, the four dumpsters that

366
00:30:43,411 --> 00:30:44,272
They have in the building.

367
00:30:44,632 --> 00:30:49,797
Again, these are dumpsters that are frequently overflowing with trash.

368
00:30:49,857 --> 00:30:51,279
Many of them have rats underneath them.

369
00:30:51,379 --> 00:31:02,269
One of the dumpsters, the dumpsters in the middle, has been just permanently sealed off when I visited there in December 2025, and it was still sealed when I visited there last week.

370
00:31:04,110 --> 00:31:09,392
It seems to be an operational dumpster, but the landlord decided to seal it off.

371
00:31:09,692 --> 00:31:13,014
The dumpsters are also way too small for this apartment complex.

372
00:31:13,254 --> 00:31:18,636
This picture here on the left is one that was taken by Dan, one of the residents of Brooks Park.

373
00:31:23,239 --> 00:31:30,644
And he said that this is a fairly normal state of affairs for the trash to be overflowing to this degree.

374
00:31:31,144 --> 00:31:38,190
The picture on the right is a picture that I took during our tour of the apartment complex last week.

375
00:31:39,130 --> 00:31:43,794
And you could see visualized here, I know it's a little bit dark, but a dead rat hanging out from

376
00:31:44,354 --> 00:31:46,596
underneath one of the dumpsters.

377
00:31:47,076 --> 00:31:55,423
So it's not really that hard to find physical evidence of this infestation that these residents have been dealing with.

378
00:31:56,223 --> 00:31:58,065
When I toured the apartment complex in December of last year,

379
00:32:04,169 --> 00:32:12,675
The residents typically hold meetings in their laundry room in the basement, which has its own odor to it.

380
00:32:12,695 --> 00:32:19,240
It's a place where rats are very frequently found.

381
00:32:20,181 --> 00:32:21,122
It smells like urine.

382
00:32:21,542 --> 00:32:26,405
As you can see, there's a corner that's just covered in rat droppings.

383
00:32:27,866 --> 00:32:38,918
The property owners have since cleaned that particular part up, but within the basement and the building in general, there's many holes that rats use to get in and out of the building.

384
00:32:38,938 --> 00:32:46,446
A lot of them go to the park in front of it, and then they seek out the building just to get some form of shelter.

385
00:32:48,507 --> 00:32:55,071
Outside as well, in some of these photos, the hedges in front have a lot of rat holes, which you could see in the top center photo.

386
00:32:55,951 --> 00:33:00,773
And there's also, you know, just during that tour, another dead rat that we found there.

387
00:33:00,853 --> 00:33:03,535
So for these residents, it's gotten pretty bad.

388
00:33:03,815 --> 00:33:04,655
It's an older building.

389
00:33:04,695 --> 00:33:05,756
I believe it was built in the

390
00:33:07,177 --> 00:33:11,839
in the 1920s and so there is a lot of work that needs to be done on it.

391
00:33:12,239 --> 00:33:28,747
But the point is with this situation, it's gotten pretty bad and there's a couple of very low investment, there's a couple of very low cost options that the landlords can undertake in order to fix this situation, namely just getting more dumpsters, getting, you know,

392
00:33:31,508 --> 00:33:36,412
getting more frequent trash pickup, making sure that the trash receptacles that they have can be sealed.

393
00:33:37,033 --> 00:33:40,195
And unfortunately, we've kind of come to a situation where they've been

394
00:33:41,871 --> 00:33:48,698
not responsive enough to these claims over the last couple of months that I thought it was necessary to bring this up at a City Council meeting and hopefully put some public pressure on them.

395
00:33:49,419 --> 00:34:01,452
Last week, the tenant association organized a tour in which a member of staff, a sanitarian from the Medford Board of Health also attended.

396
00:34:01,492 --> 00:34:04,215
That's Deanna Earl, pictured right here.

397
00:34:05,308 --> 00:34:08,489
as well as many members of the Brooks Park Tenant Association.

398
00:34:08,529 --> 00:34:13,792
They walked myself and Deanna around, just showed everybody sort of what the situation was.

399
00:34:14,972 --> 00:34:21,195
Dan, pictured here, kind of took everybody around, told folks where he usually saw the rats hiding.

400
00:34:21,895 --> 00:34:28,338
So this is definitely a case where, you know, the city knows what's going on.

401
00:34:28,378 --> 00:34:30,478
They are trying to do what they can.

402
00:34:30,539 --> 00:34:33,920
The park in front is public property and the Board of Health has,

403
00:34:36,281 --> 00:35:00,273
done its part, but we do need to get a more substantial response from Charlesgate and encourage them to put more of an investment in this property and help these residents out who've been living with the presence of rats for a very long period of time.

404
00:35:02,134 --> 00:35:07,298
But I've put a little bit too much time talking.

405
00:35:07,338 --> 00:35:21,767
I feel like I would be pleased if some of the residents who've taken time out of their evening to attend the city council meeting would be free to say a few words.

406
00:35:22,788 --> 00:35:26,490
And by all means, please, the floor is yours.

407
00:35:26,610 --> 00:35:26,891
Thank you.

408
00:35:27,731 --> 00:35:28,351
Thanks, you guys.

409
00:35:28,671 --> 00:35:30,132
I'm really glad to have you here.

410
00:35:30,172 --> 00:35:34,753
And if you could just give us your name and your address when you speak, let us know, you know, who you are.

411
00:35:34,893 --> 00:35:36,173
And we really want to hear your story.

412
00:35:36,913 --> 00:35:42,735
And we're grateful to all of you guys for organizing, Councilor Lemming for working with you and engaging the city on this.

413
00:35:42,775 --> 00:35:43,675
So thank you for being here.

