592
00:51:41,963 --> 00:51:44,825
We have one person in the chamber.

593
00:51:44,885 --> 00:51:46,847
If there's anyone on Zoom, please raise your hand on Zoom.

594
00:51:48,928 --> 00:51:56,492
name and address for the record please and you'll have three minutes.

595
00:51:56,912 --> 00:52:03,496
I'm not suggesting in any way that the council is dragging their feet on this, but I just want to point out something that how

596
00:52:04,210 --> 00:52:07,631
We really, really, really, really need to move fast on this.

597
00:52:08,771 --> 00:52:11,012
Rats don't have a breeding season per se.

598
00:52:11,252 --> 00:52:14,093
They can breed all year round, but in the winter months it's much less.

599
00:52:14,513 --> 00:52:17,974
But March and April they start really, really populating.

600
00:52:19,014 --> 00:52:21,775
One single female rat can produce 56 or more.

601
00:52:23,615 --> 00:52:24,496
rats a year.

602
00:52:25,056 --> 00:52:33,784
They come in, the gestation is 18 to 22 days, but the females can start reproducing three days after that at 25 days.

603
00:52:34,264 --> 00:52:46,175
So if you think, say if we have 100 rats and 50 of them are female and each one of those are going to produce 56 babies approximately, your population is going to explode.

604
00:52:46,535 --> 00:52:48,897
So that's basically what I wanted to say is that

605
00:52:50,118 --> 00:52:53,780
Again, I'm not suggesting you're dragging your feet, but you really need to move on this.

606
00:52:53,860 --> 00:53:02,205
And if the citation is the first step, and then start finding, because it's obvious that their landlord is not doing what needs to be done.

607
00:53:02,625 --> 00:53:10,429
And all you need is one person to come down with something that a rat carried, and what happens then.

608
00:53:10,729 --> 00:53:11,370
But thank you.

609
00:53:12,891 --> 00:53:13,271
