Jennifer Yankel, 16 Monument Street.

1041
01:25:24,164 --> 01:25:28,331
I've just been thinking about this ever since the rat discussion happened.

1042
01:25:29,593 --> 01:25:30,173
I'm really...

1043
01:25:33,405 --> 01:25:41,748
astounded that the city has no means of dealing with this more directly.

1044
01:25:41,768 --> 01:25:44,289
I mean, aren't there nuisance laws?

1045
01:25:44,509 --> 01:25:50,552
I think if my neighbors complained that my bees stung them, I would have to get rid of them.

1046
01:25:51,952 --> 01:25:56,594
It seems to me that having rats, because you're negligent about

1047
01:25:57,952 --> 01:26:02,234
you know, the dumpsters is a no-brainer.

1048
01:26:03,174 --> 01:26:12,198
So I'm just expressing my astonishment that there's no way to just say, you know, this doesn't work in Medford.

1049
01:26:12,958 --> 01:26:17,460
We do have a dumpster permit with a fee and that requires a pest management plan.

1050
01:26:17,480 --> 01:26:22,982
So I think there's very, I think there's actually very clear ways for us to require them to

1051
01:26:23,999 --> 01:26:26,041
have dumpsters that meet the permits and the fees.

1052
01:26:26,922 --> 01:26:28,623
So I'm hoping we'll explore that.

1053
01:26:28,764 --> 01:26:33,268
Yeah, I hope so, because it sounds like really the people that are living there are really suffering.

1054
01:26:33,348 --> 01:26:40,575
And everybody around them, according to the report we had on rat reproduction, will soon be suffering too.

1055
01:26:41,303 --> 01:26:45,845
Yes, I mean, it seems to me like something that, you know, next week someone should go out.

1056
01:26:45,865 --> 01:26:46,085
Okay.

1057
01:26:46,426 --> 01:26:52,048
That's my, I mean, I can't direct anyone to do anything, only the mayor can, but it seems to me like it's a no brainer as well.

1058
01:26:52,168 --> 01:26:53,729
Yeah, I think it's a really high priority.

